text: Elena Delle Donne (born September 5, 1989) is an American professional basketball player for the Washington Mystics of the Women's National Basketball Association (WNBA). She was born in Wilmington, Delaware. Delle Donne played a successful college basketball career for the Delaware Blue Hens from 2009 to 2013. She was drafted by the Chicago Sky with the 2nd overall pick of the 2013 WNBA Draft, and led the Sky to the 2014 WNBA Finals. She would later be traded to the Washington Mystics and lead them to their first WNBA Championship in franchise history in 2019. Delle Donne has won two WNBA Most Valuable Player Awards (2015, 2019). ==References== Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:American basketball players Category:Lesbians Category:LGBT sportspeople Category:Medalists at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic gold medalists for the United States Category:Shooting guards Category:Small forwards Category:Sportspeople from Wilmington, Delaware Category:Sportspeople from Chicago Category:Women's basketball players
